subsection.p:
If magnetic field is not uniform, then the energy  in the magnetic field in a particular space volume will be given by an integral over the volume.

	U_B = \frac{1}{2\mu_0} \int_{\text{Volume}} B^2 dV\ \ \  \text{(Energy in magnetic field)}

The formula for the energy in the magnetic field is similar to that of energy in the electric field. 

	U_E = \frac{1}{2} \epsilon_0\int_{\text{Volume}} E^2 dV. \ \ \  \text{(Energy in electric field)}

The sum of energy in electric and magnetic field is called the  electromagnetic energy, or energy in the electromagnetic field, U_{em}.

	U_{em} = U_E + U_B.
